match.statusText: South Africa won by 5 wickets (with 8 balls remaining)

image.caption: Black clouds hang over the Bangabandhu national stadium in Dhaka
image.longCaption: Black clouds hang over Banghabandhu nation stadium in Dhaka as the pitch is covered with plastic 20 April 2003. South African and India are to play the final match of the TVS tri-nation cricket tournament, but heavy rain stopped the match before it could start

stories.title: McKenzie wins the day
stories.summary: The least important match of the tournament produced the most excitement, but South Africa got over their early jitters and chased the target of 216 with five wickets and eight balls to spare.

stories.title: Seizing the moment
stories.summary: Today's was an inconsequential game that both sides took seriously
